	<div id="p290985" class="post row-fluid even">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=57876&amp;sid=93d9e207b265338ab34c317a4a9b5411">alpage</a></strong> &raquo; Mon Feb 18, 2013 3:35 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content">Thanks for the compliments. The original project that inspired this is here: <a href="http://www.thesvd.com/SVD/" class="postlink">http://www.thesvd.com/SVD/</a>. The SVD required 9 ICs and a bunch of other parts and in order to use it you had to plug it into a serial port on your computer and use software to change the floppy images. It had 128K of static RAM on the PCB to hold up to two virtual floppy disks. The SVD software was carefully constructed assembly code with every microsecond of instruction time accounted for to bit-bang data in and out of the data lines.<br /><br />Developing it on the Pi is so much easier as I can compile and run software on the Pi itself rather than on a development system. And of course I can download new floppy disk images directly from the internet.</div>

			

		</div>

		
