	<div id="p441404" class="post row-fluid odd">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=57876&amp;sid=93d9e207b265338ab34c317a4a9b5411">alpage</a></strong> &raquo; Tue Oct 22, 2013 12:45 am </div>

			

			<div class="content">Just today I implemented functionality to control a floppy disk drive from the Pi and dump the tracks to a file, e.g. .DMK file used by various TRS-80 emulators. Required rewiring one of my prototypes to turn inputs into outputs and vice versa and some code changes. Dumps a 35 track single-sided disk to a file in under 20 seconds.<br /><br />See latest blog entry at <a href="http://virtualfloppy.blogspot.ca/2013/10/using-raspberry-pi-to-read-floppy-disks.html" class="postlink">http://virtualfloppy.blogspot.ca/2013/10/using-raspberry-pi-to-read-floppy-disks.html</a></div>

			

		</div>

		
		<dl class="postprofile span3" id="profile441404">
			<dt>
				
			</dt>
